    {
      "id": "edge-class-contract-task-bridge",
      "type": "task",
      "label": "Define how graphs bridge to edge classes",
      "position": {
        "x": 800,
        "y": 220
      },
      "width": 380,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "body": "Default bridge: the base edge remains valid on its own, and may optionally reference an edge-class `key` through `data.edgeClassKey`. The class artifact owns semantic meaning and defaults. Bridge flows may populate a host legend with copied class metadata so humans and renderers can resolve the class locally, but that legend entry is exposure, not authority. Graphs should not hardcode semantics into styling alone when a class is intended.",
