      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Edge Class Graph Shape\n\nA standard edge-class graph should contain:\n\n- a `manifest` node with:\n  - `intent.kind = edge-class`\n  - `data.edgeClass` as the authoritative contract payload\n- one human-readable overview/document node that explains the class meaning and usage\n- optional navigation ports such as `Back to Edge Class Library`\n\nWhat it does **not** need by default:\n\n- a custom runtime behavior node\n- arbitrary execution logic\n- a second semantic authority separate from `manifest.data.edgeClass`\n\nSo the graph shape is:\n\n1. authoritative manifest payload\n2. readable overview for humans\n3. optional navigation/support nodes\n\nThe manifest owns the class. The rest of the graph explains or exposes it.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
